	<div data-zesty-id="content:block:6-bcfbdaa6d3-vjj3qs:27:7:0:40">{{block('/-/block/hero_full.html?variant=7-9a91adcec0-sg76hm')}}</div>
	<div class="p-6 rounded-5 bg-light mb-18" data-zesty-id="design:columns:1 column - 1 row my-3:25:93">
<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12" data-zesty-id="design:columns:1 column - 1 row my-3:25:93-1:1 column - 1 row:0">
<div class="row my-3" data-zesty-id="design:columns:2columnswideright:1:36">
<div class="col-md-4 col-sm-12" data-zesty-id="design:columns:2columnswideright:1:36-2:2 Columns - Left Small:0">
<img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/uss-cache.salvationarmy.org/1a187fea-4aac-4031-9b06-b17557d44a13_029f740b-c722-4666-89c7-096a5aea4429_Potomac%2BMarch23%2BWeb%2BBanner%2BFeeding%2BPrograms%2BMobile%2BBlank.png" alt="placeholder" class="img-fluid d-block my-3 rounded mx-auto" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;" loading="lazy" data-zesty-id="content:images:1:15">
				</div>
<div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12" data-zesty-id="design:columns:2columnswideright:1:36-4:2 Columns - Left Small:1">
<h5 style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:text:2:83"><br>
					<br>
					General Willam Booth, founder</h5>
<p style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:textarea:3:2">
						&nbsp;“While Women weep, as they do now, I’ll fight. While little children go hungry, as they do now, I’ll fight. While men go to prison, in and out, in and out, as they do now, I’ll fight. While there is a drunkard left, while there is a poor lost girl upon the streets, while there remains one dark soul without the light of God, I’ll fight. I’ll Fight to the very end!”
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
<div style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;min-height:300px;background-image:url('https://s3.amazonaws.com/uss-cache.salvationarmy.org/ba1ae43a-1116-430b-a313-47c06d536cc0_Blue+BG.png');background-position:center center;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-size:cover;" class="text-white rounded p-6 gap-3 my-5" data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:5:7">
            <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;z-index:2;"></div>
            <div style="position:relative;z-index:3;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:flex-start;min-height:300px;">
                <div style="width:100%;padding:40px;color:#ffffff;">
                    <h5 style="text-align:center;">How we help overcome poverty</h5>

<p style="text-align:center;color:#fff;">
	Each night in the United States, 17.4 million families go to bed hungry.<br>
	An additional 6.9 million families live on the verge of food insecurity.<br>
	That means they don’t always know where their next meal is coming from.
</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:6:62"></div>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:7:98"><strong>Food Pantries</strong></p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:8:31">No one should should go hungry in Central Alabama.&nbsp; Our food pantries offer meal items and food staples to keep cabinets and cupboards full.&nbsp; If you are in need of food assistance in Birmingham, call <a href="tel: 205-328-2420"> 205-328-2420</a>.&nbsp; If you are in need of food assistance in Bessemer, call <a href="tel: 205-425-4303"> 205-425-4303</a>.&nbsp; If you are in need of food assistance in Shelby or Chilton counties, please call <a href="tel: 205-663-7105"> 205-663-7105</a>.</p>
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:9:87"></div>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:10:84"><strong>Holiday Boxes</strong></p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:11:41">The holidays should not be filled with worry.&nbsp; Many families in our service area receive holiday meal boxes for Thanksgiving or Christmas.&nbsp; These boxes contain everything needed to make a complete, healthy, and happy holiday meal.&nbsp;</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:12:4"><b>Provide Shelter</b></p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:13:33">Homelessness can happen to anyone.&nbsp; the Center of Hope offers a clean and safe place for women, men, children, families, and Veterans to find hope.&nbsp; in 2022, we provided 44,863 Nights of Shelter to our neighbors.&nbsp; If you are in need of emergency shelter, please call&nbsp;<a href="tel: 205-328-2420">205-328-2420</a>.</p>
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:14:27"></div>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:15:74"><b>Emergency Assistance Programs</b></p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:16:67">The Salvation Army understands the impact of unexpected life changes. Maybe you lost your job. Maybe you're a senior living on a fixed income. Maybe you're living with a long-term disability. If so, we are here for you.</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:17:4">
	Throughout the country, The Salvation Army's emergency assistance programs are helping families pay their bills so they can keep the power and water on, fill prescriptions, and access transportation when necessary.
</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:18:90">
	Assistance is available to help reduce the financial and emotional burdens associated with housing rental and utilities.
</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:19:53">
	The Salvation Army connects people with the resources they need to help their families stay afloat.
</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:20:42">
	For more information, please call&nbsp;<a href="tel: 205-328-4536 ">205-328-4536</a>.
</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>